<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>每日新闻摄影精选</title><link>https://youngwilly.github.io/chatgpt-task-rss</link><atom:link href="https://youngwilly.github.io/chatgpt-task-rss/feeds/daily-photo.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>ChatGPT 计划任务原文订阅</description><language>zh-cn</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:51:15 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>ChatGPT Task RSS</generator><item><title>每日新闻摄影精选</title><link>https://youngwilly.github.io/chatgpt-task-rss/daily-photo.html#daily-photo-2026-07-13T15-51-15Z</link><guid isPermaLink="false">cf3ce66644566b089009b7cd4d270bdb31851783301934b0b563406fa4b15564</guid><pubDate>Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:51:15 GMT</pubDate><description><![CDATA[<div class="media-gallery"><figure><a href="https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/aftermath-of-earthquakes-in-la-guaira/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX1JDMkVDTUFFNUxXVg?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener"><img src="https://youngwilly.github.io/chatgpt-task-rss/assets/daily-photo-2026-07-13T15-51-15Z-official.webp" alt="2026 年 7 月 12 日，无人机拍摄委内瑞拉拉瓜伊拉拉埃斯佩兰萨公墓的十字架，该公墓埋葬着 6 月 24 日地震的受害者。路透社/Pablo Sanhueza TPX 当天图片" width="800" height="450" loading="lazy" decoding="async" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" data-published-width="800" data-published-height="450"></a><figcaption>2026 年 7 月 12 日，无人机拍摄委内瑞拉拉瓜伊拉拉埃斯佩兰萨公墓的十字架，该公墓埋葬着 6 月 24 日地震的受害者。路透社/Pablo Sanhueza TPX 当天图片 · <span>来源：reutersconnect.com</span></figcaption></figure></div><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="60">今天选这张：<strong data-start="6" data-end="60">Reuters / Pablo Sanhueza，委内瑞拉拉瓜伊拉，地震遇难者墓地里成排的新十字架。</strong></p>
<p data-start="62" data-end="110">原图受版权限制，我不放其他墓地照片代替。Reuters Connect 官方页面收录了这张原图：</p>
<p data-start="112" data-end="260"><a data-start="112" data-end="260" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="decorated-link">查看 Reuters 官方图片页<span aria-hidden="true" class="ms-0.5 inline-block align-middle leading-none select-none"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" data-rtl-flip="" class="block h-[0.75em] w-[0.75em] stroke-current stroke-[0.75] select-none"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-fec7759e.svg#304883" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></span></a></p>
<p data-start="262" data-end="468">照片拍摄于 <strong data-start="268" data-end="282">2026年7月12日</strong>，地点是委内瑞拉拉瓜伊拉的 <strong data-start="296" data-end="321">La Esperanza Cemetery</strong>。摄影师 <strong data-start="326" data-end="344">Pablo Sanhueza</strong> 从空中拍下大量十字架，它们沿着裸露的土地排开，下面埋葬的是6月24日两次强震中的遇难者。Reuters 将它列入当天的 <strong data-start="405" data-end="430">TPX Images of the Day</strong>。<span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] translate-y-0.5 animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 102px;"><a href="https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/aftermath-of-earthquakes-in-la-guaira/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX1JDMkVDTUFFNUxXVg?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" alt="https://www.reutersconnect.com/item/aftermath-of-earthquakes-in-la-guaira/dGFnOnJldXRlcnMuY29tLDIwMjY6bmV3c21sX1JDMkVDTUFFNUxXVg?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex overflow-hidden rounded-xl text-[9px] font-medium h-4.5 pe-2 ps-1 transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]! select-none" style="max-width: 102px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between overflow-hidden" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="flex min-w-0 flex-1 items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full"></span><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Reuters Connect</span></span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
<p data-start="470" data-end="555">从画面里先看到的是重复。十字架一个挨着一个，人几乎消失了，地面被切成整齐的行列。地震发生时是楼房倒塌、烟尘和搜救，这张拍的是两个多星期以后，灾难开始在土地上留下固定形状。</p>
<p data-start="557" data-end="705">截至7月12日，委内瑞拉官方公布的死亡人数已经升至 <strong data-start="583" data-end="592">4490人</strong>，另有 <strong data-start="596" data-end="619">16740人受伤、17907人无家可归</strong>。6月24日的两次地震震级分别达到7.2和7.5，间隔不到一分钟，拉瓜伊拉是受灾最严重的地区之一。<span class="" data-state="closed"><span class="ms-1 inline-flex max-w-full items-center select-none relative top-[-0.094rem] translate-y-0.5 animate-[show_150ms_ease-in]" data-testid="webpage-citation-pill" style="width: 77px;"><a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/death-toll-venezuela-earthquakes-rises-4490-2026-07-12/?utm_source=chatgpt.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" alt="https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/death-toll-venezuela-earthquakes-rises-4490-2026-07-12/?utm_source=chatgpt.com" class="flex overflow-hidden rounded-xl text-[9px] font-medium h-4.5 pe-2 ps-1 transition-colors duration-150 ease-in-out text-token-text-secondary! bg-[#F4F4F4]! dark:bg-[#303030]! select-none" style="max-width: 77px;"><span class="relative start-0 bottom-0 flex h-full w-full items-center"><span class="flex h-4 w-full items-center justify-between" style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><span class="flex min-w-0 flex-1 items-center gap-1"><span class="inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center overflow-hidden rounded-full"></span><span class="max-w-[15ch] grow truncate overflow-hidden text-center">Reuters</span></span><span class="-me-1 flex h-full items-center rounded-full px-1 text-[#8F8F8F]">+1</span></span></span></a></span></span></p>
<p data-start="707" data-end="847">这张图很重要，因为死亡人数到了四位数以后，人容易只记住数字。无人机视角把数字重新变成了空间。每一根十字架只占画面里很小的位置，几百根放到一起，规模突然变得很具体。墓地还在扩展，这点很要命。画面没有废墟，却让人知道救援阶段已经逐渐过去，确认身份、安葬、寻找失踪者这些事情还会拖很久。</p>
<p data-start="849" data-end="969">Pablo Sanhueza 没有靠某张哭泣的脸来推情绪。高处视角把个人悲伤压低，留下排列、数量和空地。十字架看起来接近，实际对应的是彼此毫无关系的家庭。画面越整齐，事情越难受。灾难把混乱带进城市，最后在墓地里被整理成一排一排的编号和坟墓。</p>
<p data-start="971" data-end="1069">它在新闻摄影上也很克制。无人机照片常常容易变成漂亮的几何图形，这张的几何感没有盖住现场。棕色土地、浅色十字架、尚未长出植被的新墓区，一眼就能看出这里刚刚被开辟。它拍到了灾难的规模，也留下了时间感。</p>
<p data-start="1071" data-end="1076">三个问题：</p>
<ol data-start="1078" data-end="1203" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-section-id="11s5str" data-start="1078" data-end="1114">
<p data-start="1081" data-end="1114">当死亡人数不断上升，航拍墓地会不会比单个葬礼更能让人理解灾难规模？</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1vzehog" data-start="1116" data-end="1159">
<p data-start="1119" data-end="1159">墓地里的整齐排列，是对死者尊严的恢复，还是行政系统处理巨大死亡数字后留下的冷感？</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="tgyazj" data-start="1161" data-end="1203" data-is-last-node="">
<p data-start="1164" data-end="1203" data-is-last-node="">搜救结束以后，媒体还会不会继续拍身份确认、失踪者家庭和长期安置这些更慢的部分？</p>
</li>
</ol></div></div>]]></description></item></channel></rss>